article.headline: Brown 71, Harvard 51
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Mark McAndrew scored 14 points and Adrian Williams added 13 as Brown kept Harvard winless on the road this season with a 71-51 win on Saturday night. McAndrew, the Ivy League's leading scorer, was 5-for-7 from the floor and 3-for-3 from the free throw line. Alex Blankenau led Harvard with 14 points and Kyle Fitzgerald had 10. Brown (12-8, 4-2) has won three consecutive games and four of five while Harvard (6-16, 1-5) has lost five straight and is 0-13 in road games. Brown never trailed and led by as many as 26 points, 61-35, on a 3-point shot by Williams midway through the second half. The Crimson missed 11 of their first 12 shots and went a span of 5:12 between baskets in the first half. Brown closed the first half with an 8-0 run, including 3-point baskets by McAndrew and Williams, and took a 37-16 lead into halftime. The Bears, who shot 64 percent in a 77-51 win over Dartmouth on Friday, connected on 55 percent against Harvard.
